The leadership of the Lagos State chapter of the National Association of Nigerian Nurses and Midwives (NANNM) has cried out over the disappearance of one of its members. The association called on members of the public to help in search of the member, identified as Tola Adetola, a staff member of the Federal Medical Centre, Ebute Meta. Adetola has been missing since Monday June 15, 2020, it was learnt. The Chairman of the chapter, Mrs Blessing Israel, said Ms Adetola, a pre-operative nursing officer at the hospital, had left home on Sunday for work but she neither returned home nor reported at work. Dear our valued reader, we would like to hear your view about a membership club that we plan to launch. Kindly help us fill this survey. The missing woman, a resident of Bariga, in the Lagos metropolis, was said to have left home in a commercial bus to the hospital at about 7pm on the fateful day. A statement from the union implored anyone with useful information to notify the management of the Federal Medical Centre, Ebute Meta, the NANNM chairman, or call the following numbers: 08114078779, 08072869636, 08055308053.  Nurses flay FG over resident doctors, threaten strike Head of service laments exodus of health workers Health workers at FTH Gombe protest over alleged bias